review_blob: Light yellow with almost no head.  Smell is mainly honey. Taste is very complex with hints of butterscotch, honey, and grapes.  Very smooth finish and easy to drink.  Another good offering from Dogfish.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: This is DuClaws best beer. The color is almost more amber than gold, with a thick head and nice lacing. Citrus hops aroma and flavor with a smooth moufhfeel.  This is a great American Pale.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Golden brown with a thin but lasting head. Fruity hops aroma. Nice smooth mouthfeel.  Malt is definitely evident, but finsishs fairly hoppy.
Hazy orange gold color with a very thin white head.  Slight citrus aroma.  Sweet and not very hoppy.  Flavor is somewhat lacking.  Not my favorite pale ale.
Light golden yellow with thin head that fades fast.  Citrusy hops aroma.  Crisp with sweetness up front fading to a bitter ending.  Good for a summer beer
Smells strongly of roasted malts and chocolate.  Very dark brown with a thin tan head.  Very rich chocolate flavor with a nice thick mouthfeel.
Light gold color with thick bubbly white head.  Pleasant hops aroma.  Very nice feel in the mouth. Strong hops feeling upfront.  Tastes very good for the amount of alcohol.
Deep brownish red color with thick lasting head. Aroma is predominantly malty. Very nice balance to this beer with a slight aftertaste of the hops.  Excellent beer overall.
Deep black color with thin brown head.  Strong chocolate aroma.  Very creamy in the mouth.  Can slightly taste the alcohol but it blends well with the chocolate.
Orange cloudy color.  Nice long lasting white head.  Moderate lacing. Nice hops aroma and strong hops taste balanced nicely with the malt. Very tasty IPA.
